### 1. All entities check
GET http://localhost:4004/hr/Departments
###
GET http://localhost:4004/hr/Employees
###
GET http://localhost:4004/hr/Projects
###
GET http://localhost:4004/hr/Skills
###
GET http://localhost:4004/hr/Assignments
###
GET http://localhost:4004/hr/EmployeeSkills

### 2. Create a Department
POST http://localhost:4004/hr/Departments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "deptName": "Engineering",
  "description": "Software Engineering",
  "budget": 500000.00,
  "location": "Bangalore"
}

### 3. Create an Employee linked to a Department
POST http://localhost:4004/hr/Employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "john@company.com",
  "jobTitle": "Developer",
  "hireDate": "2024-01-01",
  "salary": 75000.00,
  "isActive": true,
  "department_ID": "<paste-department-ID-here>"
}

### 4. Create a Project
POST http://localhost:4004/hr/Projects
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "projectName": "HR System",
  "startDate": "2026-01-01",
  "endDate": "2026-12-31",
  "budget": 200000.00,
  "status": "Active"
}

### 5. Assign Employee to Project
POST http://localhost:4004/hr/Assignments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_ID": "<paste-employee-ID-here>",
  "project_ID": "<paste-project-ID-here>",
  "role": "Developer",
  "allocation": 100,
  "startDate": "2026-01-01",
  "endDate": "2026-12-31"
}

### 6. $expand check
GET http://localhost:4004/hr/Employees?$expand=department,assignments

### 7. Views check
GET http://localhost:4004/hr/TeamOverview
###
GET http://localhost:4004/hr/ProjectDashboard
###
GET http://localhost:4004/hr/SkillsMatrix